{"title_page": "Hamid Davood Abadi", "text_new": "{{Orphan|date=April 2020}}\n\n{{Infobox writer\n| name        = Hamid Davood Abadi\n| image       = \n| caption     = \n| birth_date  = 17 October 1965\n| birth_place = [[Tehran]], [[Iran]]\n| occupation  = Writer, Translator, scholar\n| death_date  = \n| death_place = \n| movement    = \n| children     = \n| }}\n\n'''Hamid Davood Abadi''' ({{Lang-fa|\u062d\u0645\u06cc\u062f \u062f\u0627\u0648\u0648\u062f\u0622\u0628\u0627\u062f\u06cc}}, b. 17 October 1965 in [[Tehran]], [[Iran]]) is an Iranian scholar, author, translator and writer.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.farsnews.com/news/13930818001342|title=Hamid Davood Abadi was hospitalized |publisher=[[Fars News Agency]]|date=|accessdate= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://iqna.ir/fa/news/2069327|title=Az Meraaj Bargashtegan |publisher=iqna.ir|date=|accessdate= }}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nDavood Abadi was born and raised in Tehran, Iran in 1965.\n\n== Career ==\nHis works are bestsellers in [[Iran]] and caused a lot of discussion.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.farsnews.com/news/13900622000268/%d8%b4%d9%86%d8%a7%d8%b3%d9%86%d8%a7%d9%85%d9%87-%db%8c%da%a9-%d8%b1%d8%b2%d9%85%d9%86%d8%af%d9%87-%d8%b4%d9%88%d8%ae%e2%80%8c%d8%b7%d8%a8%d8%b9|title=Identity card of a funny combatant |publisher=[[Fars News Agency]]|date=|accessdate= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ibna.ir/fa/doc/shortint/245131|title= \u062f\u0627\u0648\u062f\u0622\u0628\u0627\u062f\u06cc: \u062d\u0648\u0627\u062f\u062b \u0627\u0646\u0642\u0644\u0627\u0628 \u0631\u0627 \"\u0627\u0632 \u0645\u0639\u0631\u0627\u062c \u0628\u0631\u06af\u0634\u062a\u06af\u0627\u0646\" \u0648 \"\u0686\u0627\u062f\u0631 \u0648\u062d\u062f\u062a\" \u0645\u0637\u0627\u0644\u0639\u0647 \u06a9\u0646\u06cc\u062f |publisher=Ibna|language=Persian|accessdate= }}</ref> He began writing in 1987. He wrote 17 books, with his 2012 autobiography ''Az Meraaj Bargashtegan'' attracting the most attention.<ref name=\"farsnews1\">{{cite news|url=https://www.farsnews.com/news/13920229000357/%d8%ac%d9%88%d8%a7%d9%86%db%8c-%d8%af%db%8c%d8%af%d9%85-%da%a9%d9%87-%d9%85%db%8c-%d8%ae%d9%86%d8%af%db%8c%d8%af-%d9%88-%d8%b1%d9%81%d8%aa-%d8%aa%d8%a7-%d8%ae%d9%88%d8%af%d8%b4-%d8%b1%d8%a7-%d9%85%d9%86%d9%81%d8%ac%d8%b1-%da%a9%d9%86%d8%af-%d9%85%d8%a7%d8%ac%d8%b1%d8%a7%db%8c-%d9%85%d9%84%d8%a7%d9%82%d8%a7%d8%aa-%d8%a8%d8%a7|title= About Hamid Davood Abadi  |publisher=[[Fars News Agency]]|language=Persian|accessdate= }}</ref>\n\nHe worked as a journalist for Iranian magazines, including ''[[Kayhan]]'' and [[Islamic Republican (newspaper)|''Islamic Republican'']]. He wrote the memoirs of Mohammd Saam (interior minister of [[Mohammad Reza Pahlavi]]'s government).<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.tasnimnews.com/fa/news/1396/06/16/1512860/%D8%AE%D8%A7%D8%B7%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D9%88%D8%B2%DB%8C%D8%B1-%DA%A9%D8%B4%D9%88%D8%B1-%D8%AD%DA%A9%D9%88%D9%85%D8%AA-%D9%BE%D9%87%D9%84%D9%88%DB%8C-%D8%AF%D8%B1-%DB%8C%DA%A9-%DA%A9%D8%AA%D8%A7%D8%A8|title= \u062e\u0627\u0637\u0631\u0627\u062a \u0648\u0632\u06cc\u0631 \u06a9\u0634\u0648\u0631 \u062d\u06a9\u0648\u0645\u062a \u067e\u0647\u0644\u0648\u06cc \u062f\u0631 \u06cc\u06a9 \u06a9\u062a\u0627\u0628  |publisher=[[Tasnim News Agency]]|language=Persian|accessdate= }}</ref>\n\n==Awards==\n* 2017: Red Epic Congress in [[Shiraz]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.tasnimnews.com/fa/news/1396/07/04/1530157/%DA%A9%D8%AA%D8%A7%D8%A8-%D8%AD%DB%8C%D9%81%D8%A7-%D9%85%D8%B3%D8%AA%D9%86%D8%AF-%D8%B6%D8%AF-%D8%B5%D9%87%DB%8C%D9%88%D9%86%DB%8C%D8%B3%D8%AA%DB%8C-%D8%AA%DA%A9%D9%81%DB%8C%D8%B1%DB%8C-%D8%AF%D8%B1-%D8%B4%DB%8C%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%B2-%D8%B1%D9%88%D9%86%D9%85%D8%A7%DB%8C%DB%8C-%D9%85%DB%8C-%D8%B4%D9%88%D8%AF|title= Unveiling Ceremony of A Book by Hadadpour Jahromi |publisher=[[Tasnim News Agency]]|language=Persian|accessdate= }}</ref><ref name=\"farsnews1\" />\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Davood Abadi, Hamid}}\n[[Category:1965 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Iranian male novelists]]\n[[Category:Iranian novelists]]\n\n\n{{Iran-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox writer\n| name        = Hamid Davood Abadi\n| image       = \n| caption     = \n| birth_date  = 17 October 1965\n| birth_place = [[Tehran]], [[Iran]]\n| occupation  = Writer, Translator, scholar\n| death_date  = \n| death_place = \n| movement    = \n| children     = \n| }}\n\n'''Hamid Davood Abadi''' ({{Lang-fa|\u062d\u0645\u06cc\u062f \u062f\u0627\u0648\u0648\u062f\u0622\u0628\u0627\u062f\u06cc}}, b. 17 October 1965 in [[Tehran]], [[Iran]]) is an Iranian scholar, author, translator and writer.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.farsnews.com/news/13930818001342|title=Hamid Davood Abadi was hospitalized |publisher=[[Fars News Agency]]|date=|accessdate= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://iqna.ir/fa/news/2069327|title=Az Meraaj Bargashtegan |publisher=iqna.ir|date=|accessdate= }}</ref>\n\n==Early life== \nDavood Abadi was born and raised in Tehran, Iran in 1965. \n\n== Career ==\nHis works are bestsellers in [[Iran]] and caused a lot of discussion.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.farsnews.com/news/13900622000268/%d8%b4%d9%86%d8%a7%d8%b3%d9%86%d8%a7%d9%85%d9%87-%db%8c%da%a9-%d8%b1%d8%b2%d9%85%d9%86%d8%af%d9%87-%d8%b4%d9%88%d8%ae%e2%80%8c%d8%b7%d8%a8%d8%b9|title=Identity card of a funny combatant |publisher=[[Fars News Agency]]|date=|accessdate= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ibna.ir/fa/doc/shortint/245131|title= \u062f\u0627\u0648\u062f\u0622\u0628\u0627\u062f\u06cc: \u062d\u0648\u0627\u062f\u062b \u0627\u0646\u0642\u0644\u0627\u0628 \u0631\u0627 \u00ab\u0627\u0632 \u0645\u0639\u0631\u0627\u062c \u0628\u0631\u06af\u0634\u062a\u06af\u0627\u0646\u00bb \u0648 \u00ab\u0686\u0627\u062f\u0631 \u0648\u062d\u062f\u062a\u00bb \u0645\u0637\u0627\u0644\u0639\u0647 \u06a9\u0646\u06cc\u062f |publisher=Ibna|language=Persian|accessdate= }}</ref> He began writing in 1987. He wrote 17 books, with his 2012 autobiography ''Az Meraaj Bargashtegan'' attracting the most attention.<ref name=\"farsnews1\">{{cite news|url=https://www.farsnews.com/news/13920229000357/%d8%ac%d9%88%d8%a7%d9%86%db%8c-%d8%af%db%8c%d8%af%d9%85-%da%a9%d9%87-%d9%85%db%8c-%d8%ae%d9%86%d8%af%db%8c%d8%af-%d9%88-%d8%b1%d9%81%d8%aa-%d8%aa%d8%a7-%d8%ae%d9%88%d8%af%d8%b4-%d8%b1%d8%a7-%d9%85%d9%86%d9%81%d8%ac%d8%b1-%da%a9%d9%86%d8%af-%d9%85%d8%a7%d8%ac%d8%b1%d8%a7%db%8c-%d9%85%d9%84%d8%a7%d9%82%d8%a7%d8%aa-%d8%a8%d8%a7|title= About Hamid Davood Abadi  |publisher=[[Fars News Agency]]|language=Persian|accessdate= }}</ref>\n\nHe worked as a journalist for Iranian magazines, including ''[[Kayhan]]'' and [[Islamic Republican (newspaper)|''Islamic Republican'']]. He wrote the memoirs of Mohammd Saam (interior minister of [[Mohammad Reza Pahlavi]]'s government).<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.tasnimnews.com/fa/news/1396/06/16/1512860/%D8%AE%D8%A7%D8%B7%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D9%88%D8%B2%DB%8C%D8%B1-%DA%A9%D8%B4%D9%88%D8%B1-%D8%AD%DA%A9%D9%88%D9%85%D8%AA-%D9%BE%D9%87%D9%84%D9%88%DB%8C-%D8%AF%D8%B1-%DB%8C%DA%A9-%DA%A9%D8%AA%D8%A7%D8%A8|title= \u062e\u0627\u0637\u0631\u0627\u062a \u0648\u0632\u06cc\u0631 \u06a9\u0634\u0648\u0631 \u062d\u06a9\u0648\u0645\u062a \u067e\u0647\u0644\u0648\u06cc \u062f\u0631 \u06cc\u06a9 \u06a9\u062a\u0627\u0628  |publisher=[[Tasnim News Agency]]|language=Persian|accessdate= }}</ref>\n\n==Awards==\n* 2017: Red Epic Congress in [[Shiraz]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.tasnimnews.com/fa/news/1396/07/04/1530157/%DA%A9%D8%AA%D8%A7%D8%A8-%D8%AD%DB%8C%D9%81%D8%A7-%D9%85%D8%B3%D8%AA%D9%86%D8%AF-%D8%B6%D8%AF-%D8%B5%D9%87%DB%8C%D9%88%D9%86%DB%8C%D8%B3%D8%AA%DB%8C-%D8%AA%DA%A9%D9%81%DB%8C%D8%B1%DB%8C-%D8%AF%D8%B1-%D8%B4%DB%8C%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%B2-%D8%B1%D9%88%D9%86%D9%85%D8%A7%DB%8C%DB%8C-%D9%85%DB%8C-%D8%B4%D9%88%D8%AF|title= Unveiling Ceremony of A Book by Hadadpour Jahromi |publisher=[[Tasnim News Agency]]|language=Persian|accessdate= }}</ref><ref name=\"farsnews1\" />\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Davood Abadi, Hamid}}\n[