{"title_page": "National Institute of Technology, Durgapur", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2013}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=June 2013}}\n{{Multiple issues|\n{{more citations needed|date=October 2018}}\n{{Peacock|date=March 2017}} \n}}\n{{Infobox university\n| name           = National Institute of Technology Durgapur\n| image          =    NIT Durgapur Logo.png\n| image_size     =\n| motto          = {{lang|sa|\u0909\u0926\u094d\u092f\u094b\u0917 \u092a\u0941\u0930\u0942\u0937\u0938\u094d\u092f \u0932\u0915\u094d\u0937\u0923\u092e\u094d}} {{small|([[Sanskrit]])}}\n| mottoeng       = Work Maketh a Man\n| established    = {{start date and age|1960}} \n| type           = [[Public university|Public]] [[technical university]]  \n| chairman       = A. B. Bhattacharya\n| director       = Anupam Basu<ref>{{cite web|title=Meet our Director|url=http://www.nitdgp.ac.in/director.php|website=www.nitdgp.ac.in|accessdate=1 December 2017}}</ref>\n| academic_staff = 224<ref name=nirf_stud>{{cite web |title=NIRF 2020 |url=https://admin.nitdgp.ac.in/files/information/nirf/2020/National_Institute_of_Technology_Durgapur20191206-_OVERALL.pdf |publisher=NIT Durgapur}}</ref>\n| students       = 4,265<ref name=nirf_stud/>\n| undergrad      = 2,897<ref name=nirf_stud/> \n| postgrad       = 721<ref name=nirf_stud/>\n| doctoral       = 647<ref name=nirf_stud/> \n| city           = [[Durgapur]]\n| state          = [[West Bengal]]\n| country        = [[India]]\n| coor           = {{Coord|23|32|54|N|87|17|29|E|region:IN_type:edu|display=title}}\n| former_names   = Regional Engineering College Durgapur (1960-2003)\n| free_label     = Acronym\n| free           = NITDGP\n| website        = {{URL|http://www.nitdgp.ac.in/}}\n}}\n[[File: Administrative Block of NIT Durgapur.jpg|thumb|right|Administrative building, National Institute of Technology, Durgapur]]\n\nThe '''National Institute of Technology Durgapur''' (abbreviated '''NIT Durgapur''' or '''NIT DGP''') is a [[Public university|public]] [[technical university]] located in [[Durgapur, West Bengal]], India. Formerly known as the '''Regional Engineering College, Durgapur''' ('''REC Durgapur''').\n\n==History==\n{{Main|History of RECs}}\nIn order to serve the growing demand for trained technical manpower, the Government of India started 14 RECs between 1959 and 1965 (NITs located at [[Motilal Nehru National Institute of Technology, Allahabad|Allahabad]], [[Maulana Azad National Institute of Technology, Bhopal|Bhopal]],  [[NIT Calicut|Calicut]], [[Durgapur]], [[National Institute of Technology, Jamshedpur|Jamshedpur]], [[Malaviya National Institute of Technology, Jaipur|Jaipur]], [[National Institute of Technology, Kurukshetra|Kurukshetra]], [[Visvesvaraya National Institute of Technology|Nagpur]], [[National Institute of Technology, Rourkela|Rourkela]], [[National Institute of Technology, Srinagar|Srinagar]], [[National Institute of Technology Karnataka|Surathkal]], [[S V National Institute of Technology, Surat|Surat]], [[NIT Trichy|Tiruchirappalli]], and [[National Institute of Technology, Warangal|Warangal]]).\n\n[[File:Inside_the_campus.jpg|thumb|right|Inside the Campus]]\nThe National Institute of Technology, Durgapur (formerly Regional Engineering College, Durgapur) was established in 1960 under an Act of the [[Parliament of India]] as one of the eight such colleges, as a co-operative venture between the [[Government of India]] and the [[Government of West Bengal]] aimed to function as a pace setter for engineering education in the country and to foster national integration. It is a fully funded premier Technological Institution of the Government of India and is administered by an autonomous Board of Governors. The college was given autonomy in financial and administrative matters to achieve rapid development.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Sharma |first1=Amit |title=NIT DURGAPUR \u2013 NATIONAL INSTITUTE OF TECHNOLOGY DURGAPUR |url=https://www.wiki.meramaal.com/2018/09/05/nit-durgapur-national-institute-of-technology-durgapur/ |website=meramaal.com}}</ref>\n\nIn 1998, a review committee \"High Powered Review Committee (HPRC)\"<ref>\n[http://rajyasabha.gov.in/book2/reports/HRD/178threport.htm Department-related Parliamentary standing committee on human resource development 178th report on The National Institutes of Technology Bill, 2006]. Accessed 6 July 2007.\n {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140919052915/http://rajyasabha.gov.in/book2/reports/HRD/178threport.htm |date=19 September 2014 }}</ref>\nwas set up by the Union Government for review of RECs. The HPRC, under the chairmanship of [[R.A. Mashelkar]], submitted its report entitled \"Strategic Road Map for Academic Excellence of Future RECs\" in 1998. Following the recommendations of HPRC, in 2002, the Union [[Ministry of Human Resource Development]], Government of India upgraded all the 17 Regional Engineering Colleges (RECs) to National Institutes of Technology (NITs). In July 2003, the college was granted [[Deemed University]] status with the approval of the [[University Grants Commission (India)|UGC]]/[[AICTE]] and was renamed '''National Institute of Technology, Durgapur'''.\n\n==Departments==\nNational Institute of Technology, Durgapur has the following departments:<ref>{{cite web|title=List of Departments|url=http://www.nitdgp.ac.in/departments.php|website=www.nitdgp.ac.in|accessdate=3 February 2018}}</ref>\n* Biotechnology\n* Chemical Engineering\n* Chemistry\n* Civil Engineering\n* Computer Applications\n* Computer Science and Engineering\n* Earth and Environmental Studies\n* Electrical Engineering\n* Electronics and Communication Engineering\n* Humanities and Social Sciences\n* Management Studies\n* Mathematics\n* Mechanical Engineering\n* Metallurgical and Materials Engineering\n* Physics\n\n==Library==\nThe library is an institutional member of DELNET (Developing Library Network), American Center Library, Kolkata, National Programme on Technology Enhanced Learning (NPTEL), and Current Science Association, Bangalore. It is also a beneficiary Member of INDEST-AICTE (Indian National Digital Library in Engineering, Science & Technology) Consortium, which provides Desktop Access to high quality e-resources (online journals) like IEL Online ([[Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers|IEEE]]/IEE Electronic Library), [[Springer Science+Business Media|Springer Verlag]]'s Link, Proquest, ACM journals, [[American Society of Civil Engineers|ASCE]], [[ASME]], [[Nature (journal)|Nature Magazine]], Indian Standards (Intranet version) and [[ASTM International|ASTM]] journals & Standards etc. It has a good collection of learning resources. It has also a collection of several thousand E-Books on computer science (published by Springer).<ref>[http://paniit.iitd.ac.in/indest/downloads/brochureforcoremembers.pdf INDEST-AICTE Brochure for core members] from [[Indian Institute of Technology Delhi|IIT, Delhi]]</ref>\n\n== Ranking ==\n{{Infobox India university ranking|type=College|NIRF_E_2019=47}}\nNIT Durgapur ranks in top 30 engineering colleges in India.\nNIT Durgapur was ranked 47 among engineering colleges in India by the [[National Institutional Ranking Framework]] (NIRF) in 2019.<ref name=Rankings_NIRF_E_2019/>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n==Notable Alumni==\n*[[Ruben Sen]], Production / Manufacturing Manager {{citation needed|date=July 2019}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{official}}\n\n{{National Institutes of Technology}}\n{{Scientific Research in West Bengal}}\n{{Paschim Bardhaman topics}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:National Institute Of Technology, Durgapur}}\n[[Category:Engineering colleges in West Bengal]]\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Paschim Bardhaman district]]\n[[Category:Education in Durgapur, West Bengal]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1960]]\n[[Category:1960 establishments in India]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2013}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=June 2013}}\n{{Multiple issues|\n{{more citations needed|date=October 2018}}\n{{Peacock|date=March 2017}} \n}}\n{{Infobox university\n| name           = National Institute of Technology Durgapur\n| image          =    NIT Durgapur Logo.png\n| image_size     =\n| motto          = {{lang|sa|\u0909\u0926\u094d\u092f\u094b\u0917 \u092a\u0941\u0930\u0942\u0937\u0938\u094d\u092f \u0932\u0915\u094d\u0937\u0923\u092e\u094d}} {{small|([[Sanskrit]])}}\n| mottoeng       = Work Maketh a Man\n| established    = {{start date and age|1960}} \n| type           = [[Public university|Public]] [[technical university]]  \n| chairman       = A. B. Bhattacharya\n| director       = Anupam Basu<ref>{{cite web|title=Meet our Director|url=http://www.nitdgp.ac.in/director.php|website=www.nitdgp.ac.in|accessdate=1 December 2017}}</ref>\n| academic_staff = 224<ref name=nirf_stud>{{cite web |title=NIRF 2020 |url=https://admin.nitdgp.ac.in/files/information/nirf/2020/National_Institute_of_Technology_Durgapur20191206-_OVERALL.pdf |publisher=NIT Durgapur}}</ref>\n| students       = 4,265<ref name=nirf_stud/>\n| undergrad      = 2,897<ref name=nirf_stud/> \n| postgrad       = 721<ref name=nirf_stud/>\n| doctoral       = 647<ref name=nirf_stud/> \n| city           = [[Durgapur]]\n| state          = [[West Bengal]]\n| country        = [[India]]\n| coor           = {{Coord|23|32|54|N|87|17|29|E|region:IN_type:edu|display=title}}\n| former_names   = Regional Engineering College Durgapur (1960-2003)\n| free_label     = Acronym\n| free           = NITDGP\n| website        = {{URL|http://www.nitdgp.ac.in/}}\n}}\n[[File: Administrative Block of NIT Durgapur.jpg|thumb|right|Administrative building, National Institute of Technology, Durgapur]]\n\nThe '''National Institute of Technology Durgapur''' (abbreviated '''NIT Durgapur''' or '''NIT DGP''') is a [[Public university|public]] [[technical university]] located in [[Durgapur, West Bengal]], India. Formerly known as the '''Regional Engineering College, Durgapur''' ('''REC Durgapur''').\n\n==History==\n{{Main|History of RECs}}\nIn order to serve the growing demand for trained technical manpower, the Government of India started 14 RECs between 1959 and 1965 (NITs located at [[Motilal Nehru National Institute of Technology, Allahabad|Allahabad]], [[Maulana Azad National Institute of Technology, Bhopal|Bhopal]],  [[NIT Calicut|Calicut]], [[Durgapur]], [[National Institute of Technology, Jamshedpur|Jamshedpur]], [[Malaviya National Institute of Technology, Jaipur|Jaipur]], [[National Institute of Technology, Kurukshetra|Kurukshetra]], [[Visvesvaraya National Institute of Technology|Nagpur]], [[National Institute of Technology, Rourkela|Rourkela]], [[National Institute of Technology, Srinagar|Srinagar]], [[National Institute of Technology Karnataka|Surathkal]], [[S V National Institute of Technology, Surat|Surat]], [[NIT Trichy|Tiruchirappalli]], and [[National Institute of Technology, Warangal|Warangal]]).\n\n[[File:Inside_the_campus.jpg|thumb|right|Inside the Campus]]\nThe National Institute of Technology, Durgapur (formerly Regional Engineering College, Durgapur) was established in 1960 under an Act of the [[Parliament of India]] as one of the eight such colleges, as a co-operative venture between the [[Government of India]] and the [[Government of West Bengal]] aimed to function as a pace setter for engineering education in the country and to foster national integration. It is a fully funded premier Technological Institution of the Government of India and is administered by an autonomous Board of Governors. The college was given autonomy in financial and administrative matters to achieve rapid development.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Sharma |first1=Amit |title=NIT DURGAPUR \u2013 NATIONAL INSTITUTE OF TECHNOLOGY DURGAPUR |url=https://www.wiki.meramaal.com/2018/09/05/nit-durgapur-national-institute-of-technology-durgapur/ |website=meramaal.com}}</ref>\n\nIn 1998, a review committee \"High Powered Review Committee (HPRC)\"<ref>\n[http://rajyasabha.gov.in/book2/reports/HRD/178threport.htm Department-related Parliamentary standing committee on human resource development 178th report on The National Institutes of Technology Bill, 2006]. Accessed 6 July 2007.\n {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140919052915/http://rajyasabha.gov.in/book2/reports/HRD/178threport.htm |date=19 September 2014 }}</ref>\nwas set up by the Union Government for review of RECs. The HPRC, under the chairmanship of [[R.A. Mashelkar]], submitted its report entitled \"Strategic Road Map for Academic Excellence of Future RECs\" in 1998. Following the recommendations of HPRC, in 2002, the Union [[Ministry of Human Resource Development]], Government of India upgraded all the 17 Regional Engineering Colleges (RECs) to National Institutes of Technology (NITs). In July 2003, the college was granted [[Deemed University]] status with the approval of the [[University Grants Commission (India)|UGC]]/[[AICTE]] and was renamed '''National Institute of Technology, Durgapur'''.\n\n==Departments==\nNational Institute of Technology, Durgapur has the following departments:<ref>{{cite web|title=List of Departments|url=http://www.nitdgp.ac.in/departments.php|website=www.nitdgp.ac.in|accessdate=3 February 2018}}</ref>\n* Biotechnology\n* Chemical Engineering\n* Chemistry\n* Civil Engineering\n* Computer Applications\n* Computer Science and Engineering\n* Earth and Environmental Studies\n* Electrical Engineering\n* Electronics and Communication Engineering\n* Humanities and Social Sciences\n* Management Studies\n* Mathematics\n* Mechanical Engineering\n* Metallurgical and Materials Engineering\n* Physics\n\n==Library==\nThe library is an institutional member of DELNET (Developing Library Network), American Center Library, Kolkata, National Programme on Technology Enhanced Learning (NPTEL), and Current Science Association, Bangalore. It is also a beneficiary Member of INDEST-AICTE (Indian National Digital Library in Engineering, Science & Technology) Consortium, which provides Desktop Access to high quality e-resources (online journals) like IEL Online ([[Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers|IEEE]]/IEE Electronic Library), [[Springer Science+Business Media|Springer Verlag]]'s Link, Proquest, ACM journals, [[American Society of Civil Engineers|ASCE]], [[ASME]], [[Nature (journal)|Nature Magazine]], Indian Standards (Intranet version) and [[ASTM International|ASTM]] journals & Standards etc. It has a good collection of learning resources. It has also a collection of several thousand E-Books on computer science (published by Springer).<ref>[http://paniit.iitd.ac.in/indest/downloads/brochureforcoremembers.pdf INDEST-AICTE Brochure for core members] from [[Indian Institute of Technology Delhi|IIT, Delhi]]</ref>\n\n== Ranking ==\n{{Infobox India university ranking|type=College|NIRF_E_2019=47}}\nNIT Durgapur ranks in top 50 engineering colleges in India.\nNIT Durgapur was ranked 47 among engineering colleges in India by the [[National Institutional Ranking Framework]] (NIRF) in 2019.<ref name=Rankings_NIRF_E_2019/>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n==Notable Alumni==\n*[[Ruben Sen]], Production / Manufacturing Manager {{citation needed|date=July 2019}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{official}}\n\n{{National Institutes of Technology}}\n{{Scientific Research in West Bengal}}\n{{Paschim Bardhaman topics}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:National Institute Of Technology, Durgapur}}\n[[Category:Engineering colleges in West Bengal]]\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Paschim Bardhaman district]]\n[[Category:Education in Durgapur, West Bengal]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1960]]\n[[Category:1960 establishments in India]]\n", "name_user": "Ashwinikumar1989", "label": "safe", "comment": "A minor change", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_Institute_of_Technology,_Durgapur"}
